b'' b'' b'as a final note, the oriental orthodox and eastren orthodox did sign' b'a common statement of christology, in which the heresey of monophysitism' b'was condemned. so the coptic orthodox church does not believe in' b'monophysitism.' b'' b'this is a point that seems to have been overlooked by many. the ending of a' b'1600 year old schism seems to be in sight.' b'' b'the theologians said that the differences between them were fundamentally' b'ones or terminology, and that the christological faith of both groups was' b'the same.' b'' b'some parishes have concelebrated the eucharist, and here in southern africa' b'we are running a joint theological training course for coptic and byzantine' b'orthodox.' b'' b'there are still several things to be sorted out, however. as far as the' b'copts are concerned, there were three ecumenical councils, whily the' b'byzantine orthodox acknowledge seven.' b'' b'============================================================' b'steve hayes, department of missiology editorial department' b'univ. of south africa, p.o. box pretoria, south africa' b'faq: missiology is the study of christian mission and is part of' b'the faculty of theology at unisa' 